						               													<description>A simple and fun bingo to get to know the animals and contextualise them in their environment. The kit includes six environment cards and thirty-six animals to be placed in the corresponding spaces.&amp;#10;We can decide to use the material to organise a bingo, or to present the individual animals as flashcards to be placed in the corresponding environment. In this case, the recognition of the animals is contextualised in the environment in which the animal lives. This allows the child to place the learning in a meaningful context.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;THE BINGO&amp;#10;To play the game, all that is needed is to distribute an environment board to each player and to place the animals covered on the playing surface. In turn, the children discover an animal. If the discovered animal is present in their board, they take it and place it in the corresponding space, otherwise they place it covered on the table. The winner is whoever is first to complete their environment board with all six animals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;DISCOVERING ANIMALS AND ENVIRONMENTS&amp;#10;To make the experience richer, the material in the pack can also be used in an unstructured way, i.e. by presenting the cards to the children as if they were flashcards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
